    id: "tpl-0010-what-is-the-all-in-or-fold-poker-variant",
    name: "What is the \"All-In or Fold\" Poker Variant?",
    tags: ["poker"],
    opening: "Hello,",
    body: "Thank you for your email.\nAll‑In or Fold (AoF) is a fast‑paced 4‑Max cash‑game format available exclusively in PLO 4‑Card (5bb min and max buy‑in) and No‑Limit Hold’em (8bb min and max buy‑in).\nIt is not available in PLO 5 & 6‑Card, tournaments, or any other game types.\nIn every hand, players can choose only between going all‑in with their current stack or folding, which keeps the gameplay simple, direct, and high‑intensity.\nIf a player has “Chip Offload” enabled, they will also have the option to reset their stack to the starting amount, removing any excess chips back to their balance. This allows them to maintain the standard AoF stack size at any time.\nIf you need any further assistance, please feel free to contact us.",
