    name: "Cashier - Why is my total balance different from my withdrawable balance?",
    tags: ["uncategorized"],
    opening: "Hello,",
    body: "Thank you for reaching out.\n\nYour Total Balance includes both your Withdrawable Balance and your Promotional Balance. The Promotional Balance appears just below your withdrawable amount and represents the portion of your funds that cannot be withdrawn directly.\nPlease see below for the wagering requirements applied to our different products.\n\nPoker:\nCash Games: 10% of every wager you place becomes withdrawable. The remaining 90% stays as Promotional Balance.\nExample: A $10 wager unlocks $1 as withdrawable and leaves $9 as Promotional Balance.\n\nTournaments: The wagering requirement is 1x, meaning you can use the full amount to enter tournaments without any restrictions.\n\n\nCasino & Sportsbook:\n- Losing bets reduce your Promotional Balance.\n- Winning bets return your stake as Promotional Balance, and only the profit becomes withdrawable.\n- Example: A $10 winning bet returns the $10 stake as Promo Balance; only the winnings are withdrawable.\n\nBecause of this, your Total Balance will usually be higher than your Withdrawable Balance. You can keep unlocking your Promotional Balance simply by wagering.\n\nIf you have any other questions, feel free to let us know.",
