    id: "tpl-0036-login-issue-something-went-wrong-also-affects-ga",
    name: "Login Issue – ‘Something Went Wrong’ (also affects gameplay, lobby access, or screen loading)",
    tags: ["uncategorized"],
    opening: "Hello,",
    body: "Thank you for your email.\n\nIf you’re experiencing issues with login, lobby access, gameplay, deposits, or withdrawals, please follow the troubleshooting steps below.\n\n• Ensure your device, operating system, and internet connection are fully up to date.\n• Uninstall any older CoinPoker versions, then download the latest client: https://download.coinpoker.com/en/download\n• Restart your device and reopen the CoinPoker app.\n• If you can’t log in, use the “Forgot Password” option.\n• If tables still don’t open, make sure your antivirus or firewall to check if they are blocking the client. Please be advised that we do not endorse the use of VPNs.\n\nOur software is safe, though some antivirus tools may flag it simply because the source is unfamiliar.\n\nIf updating the app doesn’t resolve the issue, your ISP or local network is likely blocking access. CoinPoker doesn’t block regions, but some providers restrict gaming platforms independently.  You’re responsible for complying with local laws, and using a VPN is entirely at your own discretion and risk.\n\nIf the issue continues, please send screenshots and any error messages so we can assist further.",
    created_at: "2026-03-02T00:00:00Z",
    updated_at: "2026-03-02T00:00:00Z",
