    name: "Unsupported network/currency deposit (Updated)",
    tags: ["deposits"],
    opening: "Hello,",
    body: "Thank you for providing the requested information.\n\nWe’ve reviewed your transaction and noticed that you sent the XX Token via the XX Network. As a result, your deposit did not reach your CoinPoker account.\n\nWhether you're transferring funds from a personal crypto wallet like Metamask or Best Wallet, or sending directly from an exchange such as Binance or Coinbase, please be sure to choose from our approved list of supported currencies and networks:\n\nUSDT: Ethereum, Polygon, BNB Smart Chain, Tron, Solana Networks\nUSDC: Ethereum, Base and Polygon Networks, Binance Smart Chain\nETH: Ethereum and Base Networks\nPOL: Polygon Network\nBTC: Bitcoin Network\nBNB: BNB Smart Chain Network\nSOL: Solana Network\nTRX: Tron Network\n\nOur Payments team will check if the funds can be recovered. Please note that the review may take up to one week.\n\nThank you for understanding, and we appreciate your patience in the meantime.",
